sentences: Graeme William Lyall (AM), is an Australian saxophonist, composer and arranger.

He became a Member of the Order of Australia on 26 January 2003: "For service to music as Artistic Director of the Western Australian Youth Jazz Orchestra, and as a musical director, composer and performer."
Lyall played professionally at the Palais Ballroom and The Embers night club in Melbourne when he was 17 years old.

In 1971, Lyall took a composing, arranging and record production role at Armstrong Studios and moved back to Melbourne.
He became a member of the ABC Melbourne Showband for years in 1977 and finally become the Director of Music at GTV-9 Melbourne, including work on the Don Lane Show.
